Heavy rain last 2 weeks from 1/8-1/10 & 1/15-1/17. Cloudy. Chilly wind coming from West. Waves coming over harbor breakwall. Light sprinkling rain as sample was collected. White thread-like floaters in turbidity vial.

Heavy rain last 2 weeks from 1/8-1/10 & 1/15-1/17. Ferry boat (Expeditions 4) stranded on reef about 50 yrds offshore & ~150 yrds from sample site. Small stream of fresh water flowing into ocean. Cloudy. Chilly West wind. 3 turtles 20ft from samplers.
Heavy rain last 2 weeks from 1/8-1/10 & 1/15-1/17. Cloudy. Windy. Brown water out for ~100 yrds. Strong shorebreak ~2-3ft.

Heavy rain last 2 weeks from 1/8-1/10 & 1/15-1/17. Consistent rain. Bucket lid was not used while raining. 1-2ft waves. 2 small dead reef fish washed up. Murky water (not brown). West wind. Lots of plant debris on beach and in water. 4 split nutrient samples were collected and evenly distributed: 2 to SOEST and 2 to UHMC WQ Lab. Rained hard while filtering syringes.

Heavy rain last 2 weeks from 1/8-1/10 & 1/15-1/17. Actively raining. Bucket lid used. Tons of plant debris and plastic on beach, in ocean, and in sample. Brown dark water. Large boat on sand 50ft to right (north) of site. Large plant pieces in turbidity vial.
Parking lot area next to the breakwall has a large gap in the ground, looks like rebuilding. Read D.O. temperature 2x. 4th turbidity reading = 0.90.

Light brown / cloudy water nearshore for about 25ft. No wind. Flat, no swell, calm water. Sunny, hot. Small piece of red algae in bucket. Brown particulates in turbidity vial.
Strong wind. 4th turbidity reading = 1.65. Mostly cloudy. Storm may be coming in. Flat, no swell, calm water. 1-2ft shorebreak, strong.

Small shorebreak, 1-2ft. Clear water. Light wind. Gnats in parking lot. Sunny, hot. No wind.
